entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: hi i am ellie thanks for coming in today i was created to talk to people in a safe and secure environment i am not a therapist but i am here to learn about people and would love to learn about you i will ask a few questions to get us started and please feel free to tell me anything your answers are totally confidential are you ok with this

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: hello yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay so how are you doing today

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am alright a little tired

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay where are you from originally

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i live in culver city but originally i i was i grew up in venice

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things you really like about la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the beach fast drivers the city i have lived in utah i do not really like anything else but the city

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me more about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: he is my best friend my entire life ever since i can remember and we we grew up together he used to use drugs with me and he is been sober for more than a year now

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: almost impossible

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i either have to have no sleep the night before to get a few hours or i i just i do not i do not sleep well i am against taking pills and i stopped smoking marijuana and so now i just i do not sleep or have not been the past few weeks

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah it is not fun

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i lay in bed until i finally fall asleep in the early morning or i watch tv until late at night or netflix

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am out of it i am tired i am groggy i am a lot more likely to my anger is a lot more likely to come out

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i understand how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have been alright this weekend is been better than most my girlfriend has stayed at my place the entire weekend so i have been happy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not i am not as irritable

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no but

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was probably i was i believe i was twelve the first time i was diagnosed i have been diagnosed multiple times though most recent time being less than a year ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my mom sought help for me she saw that i was unhappy and she became worried

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why did you stop

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i stopped in on june first when i graduated my drug rehab program in utah of last year

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what sort of changes have you noticed since you have been going to therapy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am learned coping skills so i am able to

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: like what

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: calm myself down when i am angry easier i i i know how to stay away from the my trigger points and getting away from staying away from being angry or becoming depressed

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel like therapy is useful

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it can be if the person is willing to change and wanting it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see what you mean tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: two days ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: aw that is so good to hear

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how would your best friend describe you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: trustworthy funny shit i do not outgoing smart athletic he would yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h what are some things you wish you could change about yourself

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i wish i was not i was so short fused i wish i was not depressed i wish i did not feel like i needed something to help me sleep i wish i was just completely dependable on myself

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about a time when someone made you feel really badly about yourself

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: when i was younger my father would he once hit my dog in front of me cause he was mad at me so he started hitting the dog and i do not that was probably the biggest thing xxx i was little i remember just being sad

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry to hear that is there anything you regret

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah everyone has something they regret
